## Biases

### Model 4.0 - Publication bias

```{r}
M4.0 <- run.model(mydata, ~sqrt(Z_var))
summary(M4.0)
```


### Model 5.0 - Time lag bias

```{r}
M5.0 <- run.model(mydata, ~date)
summary(M5.0)
```

```{r}
#| label: fig-fig3
#| fig-cap: Bubble plot showing a positive significant temporal trend in trend in published effect size estimates
#| code-fold: true


pred_year_model <- predict.rma(M5.0)
plot_continuous(mydata, M5.0, mydata$date, "Publication year")
```

```{r}
#| label: fig-figS4
#| fig-cap: Funnel plot of effect sizes from the biology ES data set versus standard errors of effect sizes
